==English==

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|/ˈsɪvəl/}}, {{SAMPA|/"sIv@l/}}
* {{audio|en-us-civil.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{rhymes|ɪvəl}}

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|civilis|lang=la}} meaning that it refers to "civilized city dwelling" as opposed to the rural ways of the countryside.

===Adjective===
{{en-adj}}

# Having to do with people and [[government]] office as opposed to the military or religion.
#: ''She went into '''civil''' service because she wanted to help the people''.
# Behaving in a [[reasonable]] or [[polite]] manner.
#: ''It was very '''civil''' of him to stop the argument''.

